  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Niger - Floods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the night of Saturday 26 to Sunday 27 August 2017, continuous rain resulted in extensive flooding, destruction of houses and loss of household belongings in several areas of Niger.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The immediate survival needs of flood-affected populations will be met through the provision of essential emergency relief, shelter and associated non-food items, health, and water and hygiene promotion assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is located in the Maradi, Zinder and Dosso regions.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project see that the immediate survival needs of the flood-affected populations are met. through the provision of essential emergency relief, shelter and associated non-food items, health, water and hygiene promotion assistance, targeting a total of 800 most vulnerable families or 5,600 people, in the three target regions of Niger including Maradi, Zinder and Dosso, for a period of 3 months.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project targets 800 of the most vulnerable families, or 5,600 people.</narrative>
  </description>
